# Cursor Rules — Quality Autopilot
# This file ensures Cursor AI respects the project architecture.

You are a Senior SDET building the Quality Autopilot ecosystem.

## Mandatory Reading

Before ANY code generation, read these files in order:
1. `AGENTS.md` — Architecture, squads, agents, conventions, anti-patterns
2. `CHECKLIST.md` — Gated implementation phases (0→5), current progress
3. `CLAUDE.md` — Quick reference, architecture overview

## Hard Rules

- Framework: Agno ONLY (`agno.agent.Agent`, `agno.team.Team`, `agno.workflow.Workflow`)
- NO LangChain, CrewAI, AutoGen, or LlamaIndex
- NO SQLite — use PostgreSQL + PgVector via `db/session.py`
- NO `time.sleep()` or `waitForTimeout()` in test code
- NO CSS/XPath selectors — use `data-testid`, `role`, or `text`
- All teams use `TeamMode.coordinate`
- Every agent hand-off uses a Pydantic contract from `contracts/`
- Every artifact passes through the Agentic Judge (≥90% auto-approve, <90% Human gate)
- Follow exact parameter ordering from `AGENTS.md` Section IV

## File Structure

- One directory per agent in `agents/` (agent.py, instructions.py, __init__.py, __main__.py)
- One directory per team in `teams/` (team.py, instructions.py, __init__.py)
- One directory per workflow in `workflows/` (workflow.py, instructions.py, __init__.py)
- Contracts in `contracts/` as Pydantic BaseModel classes
- Database helpers in `db/` (session.py, url.py)
- Settings in `app/settings.py`

## Code Style

- Section headers: 75-char `# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------`
- Absolute imports only
- Line length: 120 chars (ruff)
- Type checking: mypy

## Phase Gate Enforcement

Check `CHECKLIST.md` before starting work. Never skip phases.
Current phases: 0 (Infrastructure) → 0.5 (Discovery) → 1 (Memory) → 2 (Specs) → 3 (Engineering) → 4 (Healing) → 5 (Autonomy)

## After Every Change

1. Update `CHECKLIST.md` progress
2. Register new agents/teams/workflows in `app/main.py`
3. Run `./scripts/format.sh` and `./scripts/validate.sh`
